David Mitchell <mitchell@ncsa.uiuc.edu> writes:


>Hmmm, call me paranoid, but it seems to me that it is a very BAD
>idea for the checksum (which is not encrypted with a users escrow
>key) to contain session key information.


It contains session key info in the same way as the escrow encrypted 
field contains session key info- ie highly encrypted (or rather hashed)
( and with little information) So the security
would seem to be no worse than it already
is with the encrypted session key already in the stream.
